대표 메뉴:
Good quality beef rib Steak lunch with Demi glace sauce , fries and veggies.  Served with soup and salad. Booked thru ikkyu.
Good service and atmosphere. 5 mins walk from Shinjuku station west exit.
주소: 京王プラザホテル 内, 2-chōme-2−１ Nishishinjuku, Shinjuku City

대표 메뉴: Wonderful restaurant！😍 The foods were delicious！The staff are very polite and friendly！
주소: S-tec Information Building, 4階, 1-chōme-24−１ Nishishinjuku, Shinjuku City

대표 메뉴: Surprisingly authentic cooking by a Japanese chef of Chinese dishes.  We loved almost every single dish apart from the shrimp dish which imo is intended for non-Chinese taste.  Good service but they close their kitchen very early at 8 pm already.
주소: 2-chōme-7-2 Nishishinjuku, Shinjuku City

대표 메뉴: Very good service, delicious coffee and cakes, expensive but worth the experience
주소: 京王プラザホテル 本館 3階, 2-chōme-2−１ Nishishinjuku, Shinjuku City

대표 메뉴: Amazing food, nice atmosphere, great views of Tokyo
주소: Shinjuku NS Building, 29階, 2-chōme-4−１ Nishishinjuku, Shinjuku City

대표 메뉴: Self service! Delicious noodle. Accept cash only but that’s easy eve if you don’t speak Japanese
주소: 新宿ワシントンホテル B1F, 3-chōme-2−９ Nishishinjuku, Shinjuku City

대표 메뉴: European Restaurant - Yet another restaurant in Japan that is high on presentation, above average in taste but very heavy on your pockets.  The sets were in good quantities, mixing surf and turf with Japanese style salads and French pastries.  Overall, a good dining experience.
주소: 京王プラザホテル内, 2-chōme-2−１ Nishishinjuku, Shinjuku City

대표 메뉴: Fully customisable curry. You can choose the meat, the amount of rice, the spice in the sauce, all number of extras. Everything is up to you so you can get the perfect curry and rice.
주소: Shinjuku NS Building, １Ｆ, 2-chōme-4−１ Nishishinjuku, Shinjuku City

대표 메뉴: Pronto was a nice quiet spot for u to sit back and enjoy an alcoholic beverage and some pretty good food as well. All at a really reasonable price.
주소: Nishi-Shinjuku Showa Building, 1F, 1-chōme-13−１２ Nishishinjuku, Shinjuku City

대표 메뉴: Unfriendly restaurant - we walked into a half-full restaurant at 7pm and the host unfortunately refused service when he noticed we weren’t Japanese.
주소: 2-chōme-8-8-1 Nishishinjuku, Shinjuku City

이름: Starbucks Coffee - Shinjuku Green Tower Building
대표 메뉴: Well  Starbucks  taste basically the same here as in thestates . The big difference is what u cN get everything from different cups to what u can eat and even the  coffee  they just have some different drinks they don't have stateside. But the staff was great spoke good  English. This location was very clean and safe so if u are In the area stop by and get some coffee or tea
주소: 新宿グリーンタワ, 6-chōme-14−１ Nishishinjuku, Shinjuku City

대표 메뉴:
Dark ambiance inside and good food.  We had the oden, which i think is the main reason to come here.

I liked the egg jelly and eggplant dishes.  The salad and potato salad were both standard, and I enjoyed the flavorful yakiniku.

This would be a good place to come with a group, prices are reasonable and its a convenient location close to the Tokyo government buildings and shinjuku.
주소: 新宿 NS ビル ２９F, 2-chōme-4−１ Nishishinjuku, Shinjuku City

대표 메뉴: I was sick after eating their cream cake. The taste doesn't even worth it..
주소: 6-chōme-6-2 Nishishinjuku, Shinjuku City

대표 메뉴: Was super hungry after travelling from Fujikawaguchiko and was first time I have ever eaten curry in Japan. Safe to say, I was blown away, really great value aswell! The seafood curry I highly recommend! おいしかった !
주소: 大和家ビル 1F, 1-chōme-13−７ Nishishinjuku, Shinjuku City

대표 메뉴: One of the best halal foods in Japan, with very reasonable prices and great taste. It was a fantastic experience, complemented by excellent service from the staff.
주소: 6-chōme-16-12 Nishishinjuku, Shinjuku City

대표 메뉴: Best ramen I had during my trip to Japan! Visited multiple times. Broth is amazing, noodles nice and thick. Authentic small place, not suitable for big groups tho
주소: 2-chōme-16-9 Yoyogi, Shibuya

대표 메뉴:
tiny soba restaurant , but about 15 tables and stools on counter is much enough to accept soba lovers.

you want sobayu(soba-boiled water)? when ordering zaru−soba(cold one)  , no worries just concentrate on soba , later sobayu will come to you automatically.

each meal includes soba tea.
주소: 2-chōme-1-1 Nishishinjuku, Shinjuku City

대표 메뉴:
This was a nice meal, I had the tempura soba & the portions they give are quite substantial considering the price and compared to other soba restaurants. The soba is slightly thinner than i am used to, not so much a square in the cross section as it might be considered rectangular. You can see them making it in shop.

Service was very good and they serve your food very quickly!
주소: 八洋ビル, 1-chōme-12−１０ Nishishinjuku, Shinjuku City

대표 메뉴: Good food with an amazing view of the city! When I went the service was really good, the waiter doesn’t speak English but I managed fine. They have an English menu so at least you know what you’re ordering if you don’t read Japanese. Portion size is pretty big and they have free refills of rice and cabbage.
주소: 2-chōme-4-1 Nishishinjuku, Shinjuku City

대표 메뉴: A bit difficult to find as you can’t get to it from inside the hotel. You have to access from the outside. Food was good as expected for this level of restaurant. We had dinner sets which included 6 or 7 courses. We also tried a Japanese white wine which was quite refreshing. Our server spoke some English and was trying hard to serve us well. The atmosphere was quaint and peaceful, maybe because it wasn’t a busy night. Overall we had a great dining experience there.
주소: 2-chōme-2-1 Nishishinjuku, Shinjuku City
